        Set the terminal capability cap to val, as defined in tteerrmmccaapp(5). No
        sanity checking is done.
    sseettttyy [--aa] [--dd] [--qq] [--xx] [+mode] [-mode] [mode]
        Control which tty modes that eeddiittrrcc won't allow the user to change.
        --dd, --qq or --xx tells sseettttyy to act on the eeddiitt, qquuoottee or eexxeeccuuttee set of
        tty modes respectively; defaulting to --xx.
        Without other arguments, sseettttyy lists the modes in the chosen set which
        are fixed on (++mode) or off (--mode). --aa lists all tty modes in the
        chosen set regardless of the setting. With +mode, -mode or mode, fixes
